OL,5, An NI woman who had to choose between  
OL,6, caring for her husband or her sister   
OL,7, has called for greater support.        
OL,9,FMiriam Murray, who is also recovering  
OL,10,Ffrom cancer, said the appointment of a 
OL,11,Fdementia carers co-ordinator by the    
OL,12,Fcharity Praxis was "progressive".      
OL,14,FBut she feels more needs to be done to 
OL,15,Fsupport unpaid carers.                 
OL,17,FMore than 220,000 people provide unpaid
OL,18,Fcare for a sick or disabled family     
OL,19,Fmember or friend in Northern Ireland,  
OL,20,Fabout one in eight people.             
